---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SUPPORT_EMAIL } from '../consts';
---

<PageLayout
	title={`Privacy Policy | ${SITE_TITLE}`}
	description="Privacy policy for Subtitle Toolkit."
>
	<span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
	<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
	<p class="lede">
		Subtitle Toolkit is a browser-based subtitle tools website. This policy explains what information we collect,
		why we collect it, and how we handle it when you use the site.
	</p>

	<h2>What we collect</h2>
	<p>We keep data collection intentionally narrow.</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Basic analytics data such as page views, referrers, device type, and browser information.</li>
		<li>Tool interaction events such as loading a sample subtitle, uploading a local file, copying output, or downloading output.</li>
		<li>Contact information you send directly to us, such as your email address if you contact support.</li>
		<li>Technical logs needed to keep the site secure and reliable.</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Local file processing</h2>
	<p>
		The core subtitle workflows are intended to run locally in your browser. We do not require an account to use
		these tools, and we do not intentionally store the subtitle content you process unless a feature clearly says
		otherwise.
	</p>

	<h2>Analytics and cookies</h2>
	<p>
		We may use privacy-focused analytics, including Plausible, and essential site technologies to understand
		traffic and improve the product. We do not use this data to intentionally build advertising profiles about
		individual users.
	</p>

	<h2>Information sharing</h2>
	<p>We do not sell personal information. We may share limited data with service providers that help operate the site, such as hosting and analytics providers.</p>
	<p>We may also disclose information when required by law or when necessary to protect the security, rights, or integrity of the service.</p>

	<h2>Data retention</h2>
	<p>
		We keep information only as long as needed for operating the service, analyzing product usage, responding to
		support requests, and meeting legal obligations.
	</p>

	<h2>Your choices</h2>
	<p>
		Depending on your location, you may have rights related to access, correction, deletion, or objection to
		certain processing. To make a privacy request, contact us by email.
	</p>

	<h2>Changes</h2>
	<p>We may update this policy from time to time by publishing a revised version on this page.</p>

	<h2>Contact</h2>
	<p>If you have questions about this policy, contact us at <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a>.</p>
</PageLayout>
